From: Jason Germino <jasongermino@gmail.com>
Date: Mon, 09 Jun 2026 00:00:00 +0000
Subject: [PATCH] drm: sunxi: probe HPD connectors before drm_dev_register

The KMS poll thread explicitly skips connectors flagged as
DRM_CONNECTOR_POLL_HPD; it never calls detect() or fill_modes() on
them.  Hotplug events fired inside component_bind_all() are silently
dropped because drm_dev_register() has not yet been called and the
sysfs kobject does not exist yet.

As a result, connector->modes stays empty for any HPD connector that
is already connected when the DRM driver loads (e.g. a USB-C
DisplayPort monitor that is plugged in at boot).

Non-master DRM clients — batocera-drminfo in particular — call
drmModeGetConnector() without holding DRM master rights, so the
kernel does not invoke fill_modes() for them.  The connector appears
to have zero modes, listOutputs returns nothing for it, and the
display setup script never configures an output.

drm_dev_register() itself fires a hotplug uevent for every connector
before it returns.  If DP-1 still has zero modes at that moment,
userspace processes the event and finds an empty connector, then moves
on — the subsequent hotplug fired after registration arrives too late.

Fix: probe HPD connectors under mode_config.mutex immediately before
drm_dev_register().  This seeds the mode list from the display's EDID
(via the AUX channel for DP) so that when drm_dev_register() fires
its internal hotplug events, DP-1 already has a fully-populated mode
list.  Then fire drm_kms_helper_hotplug_event() after registration
to give userspace a second notification with the device fully live.

Signed-off-by: Jason Germino <jasongermino@gmail.com>
---
 bsp/drivers/drm/sunxi_drm_drv.c | 25 +++++++++++++++++++++++++
 1 file changed, 25 insertions(+)

diff --git a/bsp/drivers/drm/sunxi_drm_drv.c b/bsp/drivers/drm/sunxi_drm_drv.c
--- a/bsp/drivers/drm/sunxi_drm_drv.c
+++ b/bsp/drivers/drm/sunxi_drm_drv.c
@@ -1278,7 +1278,32 @@ static int sunxi_drm_bind(struct device *dev)

 dev_register:
-	ret = drm_dev_register(drm, 0);
+	/* Probe HPD connectors before drm_dev_register fires its internal
+	 * hotplug events.  drm_dev_register sends a hotplug uevent for every
+	 * connector before it returns; if DP-1 still has zero modes at that
+	 * moment, batocera-drminfo sees an empty connector and ES never
+	 * attempts a modeset.  The KMS poll thread skips POLL_HPD connectors
+	 * entirely, so this is the only window to seed the mode list in time. */
+	{
+		struct drm_connector *connector;
+		struct drm_connector_list_iter conn_iter;
+
+		mutex_lock(&drm->mode_config.mutex);
+		drm_connector_list_iter_begin(drm, &conn_iter);
+		drm_for_each_connector_iter(connector, &conn_iter) {
+			if (connector->polled & DRM_CONNECTOR_POLL_HPD)
+				drm_helper_probe_single_connector_modes(
+					connector,
+					drm->mode_config.max_width,
+					drm->mode_config.max_height);
+		}
+		drm_connector_list_iter_end(&conn_iter);
+		mutex_unlock(&drm->mode_config.mutex);
+	}
+	ret = drm_dev_register(drm, 0);
+	if (!ret)
+		drm_kms_helper_hotplug_event(drm);

 #if IS_ENABLED(CONFIG_PROC_FS)
